                <head>No. 1061.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Straus</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-01-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 28, 1888</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 67.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your exceedingly interesting
                    dispatch No. 49, of the 30th ultimo, touching the missionary schools in Syria
                    and the vilayet of Adana, and desire to commend your course regarding these
                    important matters. The Department coincides with you that a tour in those
                    districts would enable you to better understand the conditions <pb facs="0599"
                        n="1559" xml:id="pg_1559"/> against which you are constantly required to
                    contend, and tor that reason permission is hereby granted, to be exercised
                    within your discretion, to visit Syria, Adana, and such other portions of the
                    Turkish Empire to which you may find it necessary to go, for the purpose of
                    thoroughly studying the situation and of conferring with our consular
                    representatives upon the subject.</p>
                <p>In anticipation of a further interesting report in the near future,</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
